rComments: Super great prof. Will even listen to complaints about things which are bad in other courses. Always willing to help, and stays behind after class for amazingly long amounts of time. Super knowledgeable about course material and life-advice-wise. Works with you and your needs, not some one-track formula.

rComments: Collins is entirely disorganized. The entire first month of the class was just Collins talking to us without any notes or cohesion. His section on Recombination was confusing and he never clearly explained the experiments. Very tough grader, asks vague questions wanting very specific answers.
Incredibly smart guy, reflected in lectures and tests. If you work for it, you can/will do well. He's very accessible outside of class and is always happy to clarify/explain concepts
